---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import ParallaxBanner from '../../components/ParallaxBanner.astro';
import ContactForm from '../../components/ContactForm.astro';
import { articleSchema, breadcrumbSchema } from '../../lib/schema';

const pageTitle = 'Things to Do in Bulverde, TX | Cody Posey';
const pageDescription = 'Explore the best things to do in Bulverde, TX — Hill Country state parks, resorts, live music venues, outdoor recreation, and local family attractions.';
const pageSchema = [
  articleSchema({ title: pageTitle, description: pageDescription, url: '/bulverde/things-to-do' }),
  breadcrumbSchema([
    { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
    { name: 'Bulverde', url: '/bulverde' },
    { name: 'Things to Do', url: '/bulverde/things-to-do' },
  ]),
];
---

<Layout
  title={pageTitle}
  description={pageDescription}
  schema={pageSchema}
>
  <Navbar />
  <main style="padding-top: 80px;">

    <!-- Hero -->
    <div class="bv-hero">
      <div class="bv-hero__overlay"></div>
      <div class="bv-hero__content">
        <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
          <a href="/">Home</a> <span>/</span> <a href="/bulverde/">Bulverde</a> <span>/</span> <span>Things to Do</span>
        </nav>
        <h1>Things to <span style="color:#FF1616;">Do</span></h1>
        <p>Outdoor recreation, resorts, and Hill Country entertainment</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Intro -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="bv-page-intro bv-page-intro--centered">Bulverde sits in the heart of the Hill Country with easy access to state parks, rivers, resorts, and live music. Whether you're looking for weekend adventures or everyday outdoor access, here's what's nearby.</p>
        <div class="bv-expanded-content">
          <p>Bulverde is one of the most desirable communities in the Texas Hill Country, offering a rural atmosphere with convenient access to both San Antonio and New Braunfels. The area has grown steadily in recent years as families and retirees discover the appeal of living among rolling hills, mature oaks, and wide-open spaces while staying within reach of urban amenities. What makes Bulverde particularly appealing is the depth of outdoor recreation available right outside your door, from state parks and rivers to world-class resorts and live music venues.</p>
          <p>Guadalupe River State Park is the crown jewel of outdoor recreation near Bulverde. Encompassing nearly 1,900 acres along four miles of the Guadalupe River, the park offers some of the best swimming, tubing, fishing, and hiking in the Hill Country. Well-maintained trails wind through native grasslands and wooded hillsides, offering panoramic views of the river valley below. The park's river access points are popular for wading, swimming, and launching kayaks and canoes. During spring and fall, the moderate temperatures make this one of the most visited state parks in Texas, while summer draws crowds to the cool, spring-fed river water.</p>
          <p>Adjacent to the state park, Honey Creek State Natural Area provides a more immersive and secluded experience. Open only for guided tours led by park staff, Honey Creek features a spring-fed creek that flows year-round, old-growth forest, limestone caves, and diverse native plant communities. The guided format limits visitor numbers and preserves the pristine condition of the landscape, making it one of the most unique outdoor experiences in the region. Tours typically take place on Saturday mornings and cover about two miles of terrain over two hours.</p>
          <h3>Resorts and Dining</h3>
          <p>The JW Marriott Hill Country Resort and Spa sits just minutes from Bulverde and ranks among the finest destination resorts in Texas. The property features two championship golf courses designed by Greg Norman and Pete Dye, a full-service spa, multiple swimming pools with a lazy river, and over a dozen dining options ranging from casual to upscale. While the resort draws visitors from across the country, Bulverde residents enjoy it as a local amenity for date nights, spa days, Sunday brunch, and holiday celebrations. The resort's proximity makes it easy to enjoy a world-class experience without traveling far from home.</p>
          <h3>Live Music and Nightlife</h3>
          <p>The Hill Country between Bulverde and Spring Branch is home to some of the most authentic live music venues in the area. Spring Branch Icehouse captures the essence of Hill Country nightlife with live bands, food trucks, and an outdoor setting under the oaks. The casual atmosphere and rotating lineup of local and touring musicians make it a staple weekend destination for Bulverde residents. Nearby venues in Gruene and New Braunfels, including the iconic Gruene Hall, are a short drive away and add even more depth to the local music scene.</p>
          <h3>Family Activities and Parks</h3>
          <p>Families in Bulverde benefit from a growing network of local parks and recreational facilities. Krawietz Park, which opened in 2025, added a disc golf course and walking trails to the community's outdoor offerings. The area's proximity to Natural Bridge Caverns and Natural Bridge Wildlife Ranch gives families access to two of the most popular attractions in the region without a long drive. Youth sports programs, equestrian facilities, and summer camps at local ranches provide structured activities for children throughout the year. The Comal ISD school system serves the Bulverde area and is recognized as one of the top-performing districts in the state.</p>
          <h3>Seasonal Activities and Events</h3>
          <p>Spring and fall are the prime seasons for outdoor activity in Bulverde. Wildflower season in March and April blankets the Hill Country roadsides with bluebonnets, Indian paintbrush, and other native blooms, drawing photographers and nature lovers to the area's scenic back roads. Fall brings cooler weather and excellent conditions for hiking, cycling, and horseback riding along the trails near the Guadalupe River. The holiday season sees community gatherings, tree lighting ceremonies, and festive events at local venues. During summer, the river and resort pools provide essential relief from the Texas heat, and evening concerts at outdoor venues become a weekly ritual for many residents.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Activities -->
    <section class="section" style="background: var(--light-gray);">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-title">
          <h2>Local <span class="accent">Highlights</span></h2>
        </div>

        <a href="https://tpwd.texas.gov/state-parks/guadalupe-river" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="bv-activity">
          <div class="bv-activity__header">
            <h3>Guadalupe River State Park</h3>
            <span class="bv-activity__tag">Outdoor</span>
          </div>
          <p>Nearly 1,900 acres of Hill Country terrain along four miles of the Guadalupe River. Swimming, tubing, fishing, and hiking are all accessible from the park's well-maintained trails and river access points. One of the most popular outdoor destinations in the region and a major draw for Bulverde residents.</p>
        </a>

        <a href="https://tpwd.texas.gov/state-parks/guadalupe-river" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="bv-activity">
          <div class="bv-activity__header">
            <h3>Honey Creek State Natural Area</h3>
            <span class="bv-activity__tag">Outdoor</span>
          </div>
          <p>A guided-tours-only natural area adjacent to Guadalupe River State Park. Honey Creek features a spring-fed creek, old-growth forest, and caves — offering a more immersive and less crowded experience than the main park. Tours are led by park staff and provide a rare look at undeveloped Hill Country landscape.</p>
        </a>

        <a href="https://www.marriott.com/en-us/hotels/satjw-jw-marriott-san-antonio-hill-country-resort-and-spa/overview/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="bv-activity">
          <div class="bv-activity__header">
            <h3>JW Marriott Hill Country Resort</h3>
            <span class="bv-activity__tag">Entertainment</span>
          </div>
          <p>A world-class resort just minutes from Bulverde featuring multiple restaurants, a full-service spa, two golf courses, and a lazy river. While it's a destination for visitors, locals are welcome for dining and many of the resort's amenities — making it a convenient option for a night out or a weekend staycation.</p>
        </a>

        <a href="https://www.bulverdetx.gov/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="bv-activity">
          <div class="bv-activity__header">
            <h3>Krawietz Park</h3>
            <span class="bv-activity__tag">Outdoor</span>
          </div>
          <p>Opened in 2025, Krawietz Park is one of the newest outdoor spaces in the Bulverde area. The park features a disc golf course and walking trails, giving residents a local option for recreation without needing to drive to a state park. A welcome addition to the community's growing list of outdoor amenities.</p>
        </a>

        <a href="https://springbranchicehouse.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="bv-activity">
          <div class="bv-activity__header">
            <h3>Spring Branch Icehouse</h3>
            <span class="bv-activity__tag">Nightlife</span>
          </div>
          <p>Live music, food trucks, and Hill Country vibes. Spring Branch Icehouse is the kind of laid-back spot that defines the area's social scene — a place to grab a drink, catch a local band, and enjoy the evening outdoors. A staple for residents looking for entertainment close to home.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="section" style="background: #000; color: #fff; text-align: center;">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Thinking About <span class="accent">Living Here</span>?</h2>
        <p style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); max-width: 600px; margin: 1rem auto 2rem;">Bulverde offers the Hill Country lifestyle with easy access to everything you need. If you're considering the area, I can help you find a home that fits.</p>
        <div class="bv-cta__buttons">
          <a href="https://cposeyrealestate.idxbroker.com/idx/search/advanced" class="btn btn-primary">Search Homes</a>
          <a href="#contact" class="btn btn-outline">Ask About Bulverde</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
  <ParallaxBanner image="/images/generated/comal-river.png" />

    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section class="faq-section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions About Things to Do in Bulverde</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>What are the best outdoor activities near Bulverde, TX?</summary>
            <p>Bulverde offers outstanding outdoor recreation thanks to its location in the heart of the Texas Hill Country. Guadalupe River State Park is the top destination, with nearly 1,900 acres of hiking trails, river swimming, tubing, fishing, and kayaking along four miles of the Guadalupe River. Honey Creek State Natural Area provides guided tours through old-growth forest, limestone caves, and a spring-fed creek. Locally, Krawietz Park offers disc golf and walking trails. Cycling, horseback riding, and birdwatching are popular activities along the area's scenic back roads, and wildflower season in spring draws visitors from across the state.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>What family-friendly things are there to do in the Bulverde area?</summary>
            <p>Families near Bulverde have access to a range of activities for all ages. Natural Bridge Caverns offers guided underground tours and above-ground adventures including zip lines, gem mining, and a maze. Natural Bridge Wildlife Ranch is a 500-acre drive-through safari with over 500 animals. Guadalupe River State Park provides river access, hiking, and picnic areas ideal for family outings. The JW Marriott Hill Country Resort offers swimming pools, a lazy river, and family dining options. Youth sports programs, equestrian facilities, and summer camps at local ranches round out the options for children throughout the year.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>What seasonal events and entertainment options does Bulverde offer?</summary>
            <p>Bulverde and the surrounding Hill Country offer entertainment and events throughout the year. Spring brings wildflower season, with bluebonnets and native blooms lining the scenic back roads. Summer is defined by river activities and evening concerts at outdoor venues like Spring Branch Icehouse. Fall is prime time for hiking, cycling, and horseback riding in cooler temperatures. The holiday season includes community gatherings, tree lighting ceremonies, and festive events. Gruene Hall, one of the oldest dance halls in Texas, is a short drive away and hosts live music nightly. The JW Marriott resort also hosts seasonal events and holiday celebrations open to the public.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <script type="application/ld+json">
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What are the best outdoor activities near Bulverde, TX?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Bulverde offers outstanding outdoor recreation thanks to its location in the heart of the Texas Hill Country. Guadalupe River State Park is the top destination, with nearly 1,900 acres of hiking trails, river swimming, tubing, fishing, and kayaking along four miles of the Guadalupe River. Honey Creek State Natural Area provides guided tours through old-growth forest, limestone caves, and a spring-fed creek. Locally, Krawietz Park offers disc golf and walking trails. Cycling, horseback riding, and birdwatching are popular activities along the area's scenic back roads, and wildflower season in spring draws visitors from across the state."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What family-friendly things are there to do in the Bulverde area?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Families near Bulverde have access to a range of activities for all ages. Natural Bridge Caverns offers guided underground tours and above-ground adventures including zip lines, gem mining, and a maze. Natural Bridge Wildlife Ranch is a 500-acre drive-through safari with over 500 animals. Guadalupe River State Park provides river access, hiking, and picnic areas ideal for family outings. The JW Marriott Hill Country Resort offers swimming pools, a lazy river, and family dining options. Youth sports programs, equestrian facilities, and summer camps at local ranches round out the options for children throughout the year."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What seasonal events and entertainment options does Bulverde offer?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Bulverde and the surrounding Hill Country offer entertainment and events throughout the year. Spring brings wildflower season, with bluebonnets and native blooms lining the scenic back roads. Summer is defined by river activities and evening concerts at outdoor venues like Spring Branch Icehouse. Fall is prime time for hiking, cycling, and horseback riding in cooler temperatures. The holiday season includes community gatherings, tree lighting ceremonies, and festive events. Gruene Hall, one of the oldest dance halls in Texas, is a short drive away and hosts live music nightly. The JW Marriott resort also hosts seasonal events and holiday celebrations open to the public."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
    </script>

  <ContactForm context="I'd like to learn more about living in Bulverde..." />
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .bv-hero {
    position: relative;
    height: 280px;
    background: url('/images/generated/hill-country-home-2.png') center/cover no-repeat;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    text-align: center;
    color: #fff;
  }

  .bv-hero__overlay {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.55);
  }

  .bv-hero__content {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .bv-hero__content h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .bv-hero__content p {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .breadcrumb {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
  }

  .breadcrumb a {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .breadcrumb a:hover {
    color: #FF1616;
  }

  .breadcrumb span {
    margin: 0 0.3rem;
  }

  .bv-page-intro {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--gray);
    line-height: 1.8;
    max-width: 800px;
  }

  .bv-page-intro--centered {
    text-align: center;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--black);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* Activity Cards */
  .bv-activity {
    background: #fff;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    display: block;
  }

  .bv-activity__header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .bv-activity__header h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin: 0;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .bv-activity:hover h3 {
    color: #FF1616;
  }

  .bv-activity__tag {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--gray);
    background: var(--light-gray);
    padding: 0.15rem 0.6rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
  }

  .bv-activity p {
    color: var(--gray);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* CTA */
  .bv-cta__buttons {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .bv-expanded-content {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 2rem auto 0;
    text-align: left;
  }

  .bv-expanded-content p {
    color: var(--gray);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .bv-expanded-content h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  /* FAQ */
  .faq-section { padding: 4rem 0; background: #f9f9f9; }
  .faq-section h2 { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .faq-list { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .faq-item { background: #fff; border: 1px solid #eee; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .faq-item summary { padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; font-size: 1rem; list-style: none; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; }
  .faq-item summary::after { content: '+'; font-size: 1.3rem; color: #FF1616; font-weight: 700; }
  .faq-item[open] summary::after { content: '\2212'; }
  .faq-item p { padding: 0 1.5rem 1.25rem; color: #555; line-height: 1.8; font-size: 0.95rem; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .bv-activity__header {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
    }
  }
</style>
